            that that equation is designed for parametric use, but obviously \
            can be used as a polar function as well, with unpredictable results.  \
            If 'Coordinate Type' is 'Polar', this function calculates the first radius; \
            if 'Parametric', this function computes the x-coord of the first (x,y) pair.  \
            For the 'Mixed/mixed 1' and 'Mixed/functions' combos, it calculates \
            the radius; for the 'Mixed/mixed 2' combo, an x-coordinate"
